Information was E-filed with the court and a copy was given to the defendant; Defendant waived reading of Information; Defendant stood mute, Court enters plea of Not Guilty; motions due in 20 days; bail continued.

01:44 PM Defendant in court with Attorney Erin Nagy.  Paul W. Humphrey appeared for the State of Wisconsin. State moves to find cts 1, 2, 3, 5 transactionally related. Defn has no objection. CT finds that cts 1, 2, 3, 5 are transactionally related. Former City of Madison Police Officer K. D., duly sworn and testified. Direct Exam by ADA Humphrey. Venue established. Witness identification. Cross Exam by Atty Nagy. Witness excused. Maple Bluff Detective Sgt. K. K., duly sworn and testified. Direct exam by ADA Humphrey. Cross exam by Atty Nagy. Witness excused. State moves for bind over, waived argument, reserve rebuttal. Defn objected to bind over. Argument by Atty Nagy. Rebuttal argument by ADA Humphrey. CT found PC this defn committed a felony and bound over to branch 14.
